      "title": "Node Label — usage",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "Reads the **title** of the upstream node `depth` hops away and emits it as a STRING. The connected value passes through unchanged.\n\n**depth=1**: direct parent. **depth=2**: grandparent (useful when an intermediate node sits between the loader and the label reader).\n\nBest used when nodes are **renamed** to carry semantic meaning — e.g. rename a UNETLoader to \"Wan 1.3B\" and use the label output to drive a filename, a switch condition, or a display."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
